<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="359" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,1064,1471]" box="[160,276,1064,1090]" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1064,1090]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,1064,1471]" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">
Carapace transversely subovate, width 1.49 times length (
<figureCitation box="[835,957,1100,1125]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1182,1205]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetId="figure-126@4.[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Overall dorsal views. (a) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (b) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758418/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figures 2a</figureCitation>
, and 
<figureCitation box="[1025,1051,1100,1125]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">5a</figureCitation>
); surface covered with short, relatively dense pubescence which obscures surface and margins, with long simple setae along margins which do not obscure margin (
<figureCitation box="[938,1056,1169,1194]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1182,1205]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetId="figure-126@4.[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Overall dorsal views. (a) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (b) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758418/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figures 2a</figureCitation>
, and 
<figureCitation box="[1116,1142,1169,1194]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">5a</figureCitation>
); anterolateral margin almost entire, with small granules, junction with posterolateral margin with small low lobe but not dentiform (
<figureCitation box="[697,802,1238,1263]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figure 5a</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of epistome with median lobe flattened, almost level with endostome, lateral margin gently concave (
<figureCitation box="[168,297,1308,1333]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figure 5b, c</figureCitation>
); third maxilliped with short, subquadrate ischium, merus quadrate, subdistal margin with prominent rounded granules (
<figureCitation box="[648,768,1342,1367]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figures 5d</figureCitation>
, and 
<figureCitation box="[831,860,1342,1367]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="9.[160,225,1207,1230]" captionTargetBox="[167,1148,146,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-132@9.[163,1153,142,1176]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 7. (a, d–h) Pseudolitochira maenosonoi sp. nov. (a) holotype male, 4.5 × 2.8 mm, RUMF-ZC -5196, Okinawa. (b) P. pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (c) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a–c) third maxilliped; (d) pleon and telson; (e) whole G1; (f–g) distal tip of G1; H, G2; (a–d) denuded. Scale bars: a–d = 0.5 mm; e, h = 0.2 mm; f, g = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758430/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">7b</figureCitation>
); major chela with fingers subequal to or almost as long as length of palm (
<figureCitation box="[715,820,1377,1402]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1591,1614]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. (a, d, f) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190,Vanuatu; (b, c, e, g) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a) chelae; (b) right chela; (c) left chela; (d, e) thoracic sternum and vulvae; (f) right fourth ambulatory leg; (g) right fourth ambulatory leg (merus denuded)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758426/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figure 6a</figureCitation>
); ambulatory legs with merus and propodus relatively short, stout (
<figureCitation box="[595,705,1412,1437]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1591,1614]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. (a, d, f) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190,Vanuatu; (b, c, e, g) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a) chelae; (b) right chela; (c) left chela; (d, e) thoracic sternum and vulvae; (f) right fourth ambulatory leg; (g) right fourth ambulatory leg (merus denuded)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758426/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figure 6d</figureCitation>
); vulvae relatively smaller, ovate, positioned farther apart, opening obliquely (
<figureCitation box="[615,719,1446,1471]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1591,1614]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. (a, d, f) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190,Vanuatu; (b, c, e, g) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a) chelae; (b) right chela; (c) left chela; (d, e) thoracic sternum and vulvae; (f) right fourth ambulatory leg; (g) right fourth ambulatory leg (merus denuded)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758426/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Figure 6c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
